The paper deals with machine teaching, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves the development of teaching algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the role of adaptivity in teaching, which is a topic of interest in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to interpret the learner's transitions over hypotheses, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves simulation and user studies, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY).
